As in, the boundary metric is de Sitter space times a circle.   Recall that de Sitter space has a family of inequivalent -vacua.
  For example, in the global de Sitter coordinates appearing within the final parentheses in () the in and  out vacua appropriate to early and late times have non-trivial Bogolubov coefficients.   In even dimensional de Sitter spaces
such as the 2d de Sitter factor in () this leads to cosmological particle production.   It is worth noting that the only
conformally invariant de Sitter vacuum is the Euclidean, or Bunch-Davies vacuum, so this might suggest that this is only valid vacuum state
for the dual CFT.   However, the presence of the additional circle in () already provides a scale (see
).  So there is a priori  no reason to discard the other vacua, except in view of various other potential difficulties
with them.

